\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n                \n                 \n                \t\n\u003ch5\u003e\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t        \t\t\t\t\n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/roku-tv-features-really-want/\" title=\"Roku TVs Are Getting Smart Camera Integrations, but I Really Want These Features\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\n\t\t\tRoku TVs Are Getting Smart Camera Integrations, but I Really Want These Features\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eIntegrated cameras are cool, but I\u0026#39;d rather see Roku products improve in these ways.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAren\u0026#39;t sure if your smart TV has either one? There are \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/how-to-check-your-tv-for-cameras/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eways to spot a smart TV\u0026#39;s camera\u003c/a\u003e. Alternatively, search for the TV\u0026#39;s model number and check its specs. If there is a built-in camera, it can be disabled from the main menu, though you may have to dig around to find the specific setting.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eIn the case of a built-in microphone, there\u0026#39;s typically a switch. Both Samsung and Amazon Fire TVs have a physical button along the side that toggles voice assistance. In other models and brands, like the \u003ca href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0CY4RD4KT?th=1\u0026amp;tag=makeusw-20\u0026amp;ascsubtag=UUmuoUeUpU2036865\u0026amp;asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.makeuseof.com%2Fhow-keep-using-smart-tv-once-security-updates-end%2F\u0026amp;asc_campaign=Feed\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eHisense U7N\u003c/a\u003e, the microphone is disabled in the \u003cstrong\u003eAccessibility\u003c/strong\u003e menu.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"switch-to-a-streaming-device\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e4 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Switch to a Streaming Device\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-roku-streaming-device-on-top-of-a-tv-stand-next-to-a-television.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;Brady Meyers \\/ MakeUseOf\u0026lt;br \\/\u0026gt;\\n\u0026amp;nbsp;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-roku-streaming-device-on-top-of-a-tv-stand-next-to-a-television.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-roku-streaming-device-on-top-of-a-tv-stand-next-to-a-television.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-roku-streaming-device-on-top-of-a-tv-stand-next-to-a-television.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-roku-streaming-device-on-top-of-a-tv-stand-next-to-a-television.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-roku-streaming-device-on-top-of-a-tv-stand-next-to-a-television.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-roku-streaming-device-on-top-of-a-tv-stand-next-to-a-television.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-roku-streaming-device-on-top-of-a-tv-stand-next-to-a-television.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-roku-streaming-device-on-top-of-a-tv-stand-next-to-a-television.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A Roku Streaming Device on top of a TV stand, next to a television.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-roku-streaming-device-on-top-of-a-tv-stand-next-to-a-television.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-roku-streaming-device-on-top-of-a-tv-stand-next-to-a-television.jpg\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                        \u003cfigcaption\u003eBrady Meyers / MakeUseOf\u003cbr/\u003e\n \u003c/figcaption\u003e\n                        \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSince a smart TV\u0026#39;s network features have a short lifespan, rather than replace the TV with a new model every few years, why not opt for a streaming device instead? I still use my Roku Express from 2022, \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/alternative-ways-use-roku-streaming-device/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eas there are many different ways you can use a Roku\u003c/a\u003e beyond streaming.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThe benefits of switching to a streaming device include security and budget savings. Would you rather spend hundreds to replace your smart TV every few years or spend the equivalent of a two-person meal at a decent diner at the same rate? You can completely disconnect the smart TV from your network and avoid it being part of a breach.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"create-a-separate-network-for-your-smart-tv\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e3 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Create a Separate Network For Your Smart TV\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eLet\u0026#39;s say you\u0026#39;re worried about security but still want to use your smart TV\u0026#39;s streaming features. What do you do? Well, you can \u003ca href=\"http://www.makeuseof.com/how-segment-home-network-to-maximize-data-security/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003esegment your network for security reasons\u003c/a\u003e while retaining the ability to access the internet.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eEssentially, your secondary network is like a room, while your main network is the house. The walls of said room act as a barrier, too. If that network were to be attacked, that doesn\u0026#39;t mean your main network is in danger as well.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"format-your-smart-tv\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e2 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Format Your Smart TV\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                                                        \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/factory-reset-option-in-android-tv-settings.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/factory-reset-option-in-android-tv-settings.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/factory-reset-option-in-android-tv-settings.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/factory-reset-option-in-android-tv-settings.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/factory-reset-option-in-android-tv-settings.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/factory-reset-option-in-android-tv-settings.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/factory-reset-option-in-android-tv-settings.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/factory-reset-option-in-android-tv-settings.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/factory-reset-option-in-android-tv-settings.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Factory Reset option in Android TV settings\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/factory-reset-option-in-android-tv-settings.png\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/factory-reset-option-in-android-tv-settings.png\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEven if you plan on keeping your smart TV connected to your network, I recommend formatting it, especially if you aren\u0026#39;t using any apps that require sharing personal information. It goes a step beyond just logging out of apps by purging everything.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eBefore performing a factory reset, be aware that any picture settings will also be reset. If you went to great lengths to get the picture right, take a picture of your settings or write them down. Regardless of your brand, formatting your smart TV can be done from the main menu, under \u003cstrong\u003eSettings \u003c/strong\u003eor \u003cstrong\u003eOptions\u003c/strong\u003e. The formatting options are typically listed as \u003cstrong\u003eReset\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003eFactory Reset\u003c/strong\u003e, or \u003cstrong\u003eFactory Default\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"disconnect-your-smart-tv-from-the-internet\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e1 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            Disconnect Your Smart TV From the Internet\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eMy final piece of advice is that if your smart TV no longer receives security updates, you can disconnect it from the internet to avoid any issues. If it\u0026#39;s not online directly, and you\u0026#39;re not using it to stream online content, there isn\u0026#39;t really a way for it to be breached.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eIt\u0026#39;s not an ideal solution (unless paired with a streaming box, an HDMI cable, and an alternative broadcast method), but it does ensure your smart TV will be safe and secure. You\u0026#39;ll basically turn your smart TV into a dumb TV, which is really handy in many ways.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"a252-4e54-808df90a7dac\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/streaming-options-for-dumb-tv/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a-series-of-streaming-service-apps-in-a-row-on-the-playstation-5-media-tab.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a-series-of-streaming-service-apps-in-a-row-on-the-playstation-5-media-tab.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a-series-of-streaming-service-apps-in-a-row-on-the-playstation-5-media-tab.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a-series-of-streaming-service-apps-in-a-row-on-the-playstation-5-media-tab.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a-series-of-streaming-service-apps-in-a-row-on-the-playstation-5-media-tab.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a-series-of-streaming-service-apps-in-a-row-on-the-playstation-5-media-tab.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a-series-of-streaming-service-apps-in-a-row-on-the-playstation-5-media-tab.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a-series-of-streaming-service-apps-in-a-row-on-the-playstation-5-media-tab.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a-series-of-streaming-service-apps-in-a-row-on-the-playstation-5-media-tab.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A series of streaming service apps in a row, on the PlayStation 5 Media tab\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a-series-of-streaming-service-apps-in-a-row-on-the-playstation-5-media-tab.png\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/a-series-of-streaming-service-apps-in-a-row-on-the-playstation-5-media-tab.png\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBeing able to connect to my favorite streaming services with just a smart TV has been great, but it has also become a liability. My smart TV is now at an age where its updates are infrequent, and these steps helped me keep using it beyond its expected retirement date.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
